      "span_text": "Relative to the first-pass baseline in MT08, rescoring HiFST lattices yields a gain of 2.1 BLEU, compared to a gain of 0.7 BLEU with HCP k-best lists. ) is driven mainly by the presence of high posterior n-grams in the lattice; the low posterior n-grams have poor discriminatory power."
